How shimmer / Loading works

Theming support for shimmer

Shimmer also supports theming based on the SharePoint theme. This can be accomplished in two ways. The following three themes are supported.

  • No theme or hoo-ph-primary - use for the primary theme base background colors;
  • hoo-ph-neutral - use for the neutral based background color gradient.
  • hoo-ph-fancy - use for the fancy gradients based background color gradient.

This style sheet classes can be added to a complete block as well es directly on the placeholder container.

Block theming

Apply any of the theming classes on the surrounding block.

Font sizes

.hoo-fontsize-68 is used for Data visualization and/or large numerics. Use sparingly when specific figures need to stand out. Recommended line height is 76px.

.hoo-fontsize-42 is used for Full-screen hero moments: OneDrive album titles, dates in All Photos view, SharePoint site titles, first run hero moments, greeting moments at the start screen. Recommended line height is 52px.

.hoo-fontsize-32 is used in Titles for favorite document cards, Greeting moments. Recommended line height is 40px.

.hoo-fontsize-28 page titles. Recommended line height is 36px

.hoo-fontsize-24 Marketing email header. Recommended line height is 32px.

.hoo-fontsize-20 is used in page and pane headers, suite nav, titles in teaching bubbles, dialogs and file hover cards. Recommended line height is 28px.

.hoo-fontsize-18 Header for Teams channel names. Recommended line height is 24px.

.hoo-fontsize-16 is used in subject line in mail, SharePoint article body, marketing emails as file name and body text. Recommended line height is 22px.

.hoo-fontsize-14 is used in Commands and controls (left nav, Teams channels, command bar, checkbox, dropdown menu, toggle, radio button, button text and links), in file or document titles and as body text. Recommended line height is 20px.

.hoo-fontsize-12 is used in Metadata in file lists and grid views, denotes any activity on items (number of views, shares or @mentions, timestamps), sharing permissions, persona names and in tooltips. Recommended line height is 16px.

.hoo-fontsize-10 Limited usage, use in places where text is mandatory and space is tight. For example, it is used for any disclaimer text that may appear in a purchase flow. Its also used as the initials in a list of SharePoint sites in the left nav. Recommended line height is 14px.

    Dialogs

    Dialog Basics

    Dialog

    The following buttons launch both possible option of Dialogs.

    • Dialog: Shows an absolute positioned dialog on the screen
    • Modal: Shows an absolute fixed dialog on the screen, which has a backdrop to chancel any interference with the underlying content
    Through the change to regular <dialog> elements greater flexibility could be achieved. See MDN Dialog
    This dialog comes without a backdrop and can be used for a statusbar for example.

    By clicking on the buttons you get a demonstation of possible options of the dialog.

    To change the dialog appearance you can pass in the following css variables via the style attribute:

    • style="--hoo-dlg-height: 30vh" - result in the dialog with 30% of the viewport height
    • style="--hoo-dlg-width: 30vw" - result in the dialog with 30% of the viewport width
